<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="122">Haec species inter congeneros madagascarienses quoad nuculas dorsaliter plusminusve uniformiter glochidiatas atque folia margine non integra ad</emphasis>
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cynoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="122" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monophlebium">Cynoglossum monophlebium</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="122">
maxime accedit, sed ab eo foliis inferioribus in rosulam basalem dispositis e basi obtusa rotundatave secus petiolum per 
<quantity box="[410,500,389,412]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="122" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5-10 mm</quantity>
abrupte decurrentibus margine minute erosis undulatisve distinguitur.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
